          <p class='first-para'>
            I hear what the noble Lord says and I know the reason why he alights upon secondary legislation. It is because we are dealing with
            
            <a class='permalink column-permalink' id='column_327gc' title='Col. 327GC &mdash; HL Deb 21 January 2004 vol 657 c327GC' name='column_327gc' href='#column_327gc' rel='bookmark'>327GC</a>
            changing practice as opposed to having something static. We, too, think a proper emphasis may be in changing practice, and therefore the protocols that are being brought out, the guidance that is being given and the inter-agency working are issues on which we will concentrate. But those issues need not necessarily be in secondary legislation.</p><p>
            We need to have a good <span class="italic">modus operandi&#x2014;a</span> good way of working together in partnership&#x2014;which we all understand and can use to the betterment of the children and families we seek to serve.
          </p>
        </blockquote>
      </div>
      
      <div class='hentry member_contribution' id='S5LV0657P0-04563'>
        <a name='S5LV0657P0_20040121_GCR_44'>  </a>
        <blockquote cite='http://hansard.millbanksystems.com/people/mr-desmond-ackner' class='contribution_text entry-content'>
