            <a class='permalink column-permalink' id='column_339gc' title='Col. 339GC &mdash; HL Deb 21 January 2004 vol 657 c339GC' name='column_339gc' href='#column_339gc' rel='bookmark'>339GC</a>
            regard to serious harm and I shall not encroach upon that. Secondly, I mention this matter only because I shall discuss the position of people who I consider to be vulnerable adults; that is, people who suffer from domestic violence and may find themselves in difficulties as a result of the operation of Clauses 4 and 5. I agree with the noble Baroness entirely that the definition in Clause 4 that we are discussing is intended to refer only to the dead and not the living. However, I believe that there is not quite another world but certainly a cross-over in that regard. I beg leave to withdraw the amendment.
          </p>
