            Under those circumstances, this amendment is good because it draws attention to this issue and, in particular, it provides that the court shall have regard to the extent to which D&#x2014;I agree with the point made about the titling of Ds and Vs and so forth&#x2014;may have been subjected in the past to mental or physical domestic violence. I accept that putting too much detail in the Bill and fettering, or appearing to fetter, the discretion of judges is not what is intended and should not be
            <a class='permalink column-permalink' id='column_356gc' title='Col. 356GC &mdash; HL Deb 21 January 2004 vol 657 c356GC' name='column_356gc' href='#column_356gc' rel='bookmark'>356GC</a>
